videos.description: Texas Tech's Zhaire Smith goes up to attempt the strong one-handed dunk, but the rim comes away with its first block of the game.
videos.headline: Zhaire Smith denied by the rim

videos.description: After missing one game, Texas' Mohamed Bamba checks in and makes a difference for the Longhorns, grabbing an offensive rebound and scoring the bucket.
videos.headline: Bamba returns to spark Longhorns

videos.description: Texas Tech's Norense Odiase goes for the layup, but Texas' Mohamed Bamba sneaks up and swats away the attempt.
videos.headline: Bamba gets a strong block

videos.description: Texas' Jericho Sims puts on the million dollar moves but can't score at the rim for an emphatic dunk.
videos.headline: Sims gets denied by the rim

videos.description: Texas Tech's Niem Stevenson uses the jab step to create space and knock down the 3-pointer as the shot clock buzzer sounds.
videos.headline: Stevenson beats the shot clock from deep

videos.description: Texas' Mohamed Bamba does not seem too be slowed down by his toe injury, as he splashes in the 3-pointer before the halftime buzzer-beater.
videos.headline: Bamba drills the three before half

videos.description: Texas head coach Shaka Smart criticizes his team's lack of hustle saying,  "We do not have five out there playing like warriors," as the Longhorns trail the Red Raiders at the half.
videos.headline: Smart critical of the Longhorns

videos.description: Texas Tech's Keenan Evans shows off his skills without the ball, by taking advantage of the screen and getting the easy basket.
videos.headline: Evans wows with off-ball moves

videos.description: Texas' Jacob Young puts up the three from the wing and draws contact after making the basket, and celebrates with a stank face.
videos.headline: Jacob Young creates a potential four-point play

videos.description: Texas' Jacob Young proving to be the spark that the Longhorns need as he shoots 6-for-6 from behind the arc.
videos.headline: Young stays perfect from deep

videos.description: With Texas in transition, Kerwin Roach II thinks he has the easy layup, but Texas Tech's Zhaire Smith comes from behind to make the giant block off the backboard.
videos.headline: Zhaire Smith makes the huge block

videos.description: Texas' Mohamed Bamba collects the lob from Jacob Young, and finishes with the two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Bamba throws down the alley-oop

videos.description: With the potential to bring it to a one possession game, Texas' Jacob Young misses the floater against Texas Tech.
videos.headline: Young misses at a crucial time

videos.description: Texas Tech's Keenan Evans speaks with Kris Budden about how he felt playing against Texas with his injured toe.
videos.headline: Evans speaks on playing with 'bum toe'
